description:
File: lichen/subsys/lichen/oscore/oscore.c
Lines: 1886-1899

The oscore_unprotect_response function validates that request_piv_len <= OSCORE_PIV_MAX_LEN but does NOT check if request_piv is NULL when request_piv_len > 0.

Code path:
```c
if (request_piv_len > OSCORE_PIV_MAX_LEN) {  // Only checks max
    return OSCORE_ERR_INVALID_PARAM;
}

/* Response uses request's PIV for nonce */
compute_nonce(ctx->sender_id, ctx->sender_id_len,
              request_piv, request_piv_len, ctx->common_iv, nonce);  // request_piv used
```

Inside compute_nonce (line 1187-1191):
```c
if (piv_len > 0 && piv_len <= 5) {
    size_t piv_start = OSCORE_NONCE_LEN - piv_len;
    for (size_t i = 0; i < piv_len; i++) {
        nonce[piv_start + i] ^= piv[i];  // NULL dereference if piv is NULL
    }
}
```

Impact: If caller passes (NULL, 5) for request_piv, the code crashes.

Fix: Add validation at line 1893:
```c
if (request_piv_len > OSCORE_PIV_MAX_LEN ||
    (request_piv_len > 0 && request_piv == NULL)) {
    return OSCORE_ERR_INVALID_PARAM;
}
```
